## **Study Tips from the Lecture**

‚úÖ **DO:**

- Read cases on paper (develop reading skills)
- Watch web videos for structure/overview
- Use Slim Stomper consistently from Week 1
- Practice IRAC method in working groups
- Focus on ‚ÄúAs to the Law‚Äù sections in judgments
- Ask questions in working groups

‚ùå **DON‚ÄôT:**

- Try to memorize every detail of cases
- Worry about domestic law sections
- Read procedure/Article 41 sections (unless curious)
- Only rely on web videos without reading cases

-----

## **Key Takeaway**

**Criminal procedure law is always about BALANCE:**

- State power (necessary for safety) vs. Individual rights (protection from arbitrary action)
- Efficiency vs. Fairness
- Truth-finding vs. Rights protection

This balance is assessed based on **the circumstances of each case** - this is fundamental legal thinking.

